org.knime.core.node.util

Class CompositeIcon

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.util.CompositeIcon
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Icon, SwingConstants
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
final class CompositeIcon
extends Object
implements Icon, SwingConstants
    CompositeIcon is an Icon implementation which draws two icons with a specified relative position: LEFT, RIGHT, TOP, BOTTOM specify how icon1 is drawn relative to icon2 CENTER: icon1 is drawn first, icon2 is drawn over it and with horizontal and vertical orientations within the alloted space It's useful with VTextIcon when you want an icon with your text: if icon1 is the graphic icon and icon2 is the VTextIcon, you get a similar effect to a JLabel with a graphic icon and text From: http://archive.oreilly.com/pub/a/mac/2002/03/22/vertical_text.html
